-- Dodd Prepared to Drop Proposal to Politically Appoint New York Fed Chief
-- Phil Mattingly
-- 2010-06-16T22:08:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/dodd-prepared-to-drop-proposal-to-politically-appoint-new-york-fed-chief.html

          
          
             Senate Banking Committee Chairman
 Christopher Dodd  is prepared to drop a proposal to make the
Federal Reserve Bank of New York president a political appointee
after Fed officials objected to the change.  
 Senate negotiators on an overhaul of financial legislation
will accept House Financial Services Committee Chairman  Barney Frank â€™s offer to instead reduce the role of banks in appointing
all 12 regional Fed presidents, according to a counteroffer
released by Dodd, a Connecticut Democrat.  
